# Copyright Header

When editing a file that has an existing copyright header, add a Shekyl
Foundation line if one is not already present. Preserve the original
copyright (e.g., Monero Project).

## Rules

- Add `Copyright (c) 2025-2026, The Shekyl Foundation` immediately **before**
  the existing copyright line(s).
- Use the file's existing comment style (`//`, `#`, `--`, etc.).
- If the file already has a Shekyl Foundation copyright line, do not
  duplicate it.
- If a file is **brand new** (no prior copyright), use only the Shekyl
  Foundation line with the current year.
- Both projects operate under BSD-3-Clause. If this is a prior Monero file,
  add `Parts of this file are originally copyright (c) [dates], The Monero
  Project` at the bottom, similar to where the CryptoNote attribution sits.

## Examples

C++ / existing Monero file:

```cpp
// Copyright (c) 2025-2026, The Shekyl Foundation
// Copyright (c) 2014-2022, The Monero Project
//
// All rights reserved.
// ...
```

CMake / existing Monero file:

```cmake
# Copyright (c) 2025-2026, The Shekyl Foundation
# Copyright (c) 2014-2022, The Monero Project
#
# All rights reserved.
# ...
```

Rust / new Shekyl file:

```rust
// Copyright (c) 2025-2026, The Shekyl Foundation
//
// All rights reserved.
// ...
```
